central government
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:at least in 20C. as used in NZ (as elsewhere) for the Government of the whole country as distinct from Local Government by Local Bodies (Authorities); up to c1876 usually means the central government by the General Assembly, distinct from Provincial Government by Provincial Councils;
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:cf. Centralism
